    "body": "The rest:\n\n```\n22:54 <+pchote> then divide it into N rects based on rows\n22:54 <+pchote> merging adjacent rows of the same size\n22:55 <+pchote> and then for each rect take the corners and transform to world coords\n```\n\nNote that this works for both isometric and classic perspective (and also auto-calculates the sizes and accounts for weird footprint shapes).\n"
